Layer 7 (Application)
 - Users need an interface to send data

Layer 6 (Presentation)
 - Data needs to be universal, secure format both sides understand. translates data so that it's readable 

Layer 5 (Session)
 - conversations need to be tracked so data doesn't get mixed up

Layer 4 (Transport)
 - Data needs to be broken down, reliably delivered, and reassembled 

Layer 3 (Network)
 - There needs to be a routhing system to reach any device on earth. Finds the best path to reach target.

Layer 2 (Data link)
 - Within local network, devices need to identify each other

Layer 1 (Physical)
 - transmits raw data over a physical medium